      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It is a core feature of modern regulatory frameworks that the responsibility for compliance rests with the regulated entities, which in this case are the manufacturers. The federal government's role is to set the necessary standards for public health and environmental protection, not to subsidize every private business's transition. To achieve a truly equitable system, the burden of ensuring a clean environment must be shared, and that requires industry to adapt to the rules set by the governing body.",
      "source": "target",
